- original decliment timer ---
Stdby)
time_inner = 2011/1/1 0:totaltime
time1      = 2011/1/1 0:time1 (amber time)
time2      = 2011/1/1 0:time2 (red time)
time3      = 2011/1/1 0:time3 (end time)

display total_time by pushing stdby button...

start_time = Date();


show_time displays min and sec of 'time_inner'


start)
 start_time = Date() - (time_inner - (2011/1/1 0:totaltime))
  // start time itself..

update_time)
 time_inner = (2011/1/1 0:totaltime) - (cur_time - start_time)

last_time used for belling chime;

-- simplified --
Virtual time counter using Date()
 relative from baseTime:
   baseTime   = 2011/1/1 0:0:0

Stdby)
totalTime  = 2011/1/1 0:totalTime
time1      = 2011/1/1 0:time1 (amber time)
time2      = 2011/1/1 0:time2 (red time)
time3      = 2011/1/1 0:time3 (end time)

Running)
timeInner = virtual time relative from baseTime.

timeInner is compared to time1, time2, time3 for
 bell, message, or state change.

   Added Copyrite. Somewhat fixed debug/mute switch .. Changed variable names without using underscore.
   
    modified:   css/timekeeper.css index.html js/timekeeper.js

--
Start)
 startClock = Date();
 zeroClock = Date(startClock + (time2 - baseTime));
 　　
Timer Update) 
- Triggered by a helper function $.timer()

- Updating timeInner as follows, which is a key:
  curClock = Date(); // current real clock
  timeInner=new Date(totalTime - (curClock - startClock));

Display)
 if (negTime == true)
 　  dispTime = new Date(baseTime - timeInner); 
　else
     dispTime = timeInner;
 Then merging hours to minutes for minutes greater than 59 min.

pause)
 totalTime = timeInner; // set restarting time

update_time)
 time_inner = (2011/1/1 0:totaltime) - (cur_clock - start_clock)

No need for last_time
